'''John Reginald Courage''' (1915 &ndash; May 20, 1970) was an educator, lawyer and political figure in [[Newfoundland and Labrador|Newfoundland]]. He represented [[Fortune Bay and Hermitage]] in the [[Newfoundland and Labrador House of Assembly]] from 1949 to 1962 as a Liberal.

He was born in Long Harbour Beach, [[Fortune Bay]] and educated in [[North Sydney, Nova Scotia]], in [[Pass Island, Newfoundland and Labrador|Pass Islands]] and at [[Memorial University]]. Courage taught school from 1931 to 1945. In 1945, he was named principal of the Adult Education Centre. Courage was called to the Newfoundland bar in 1953. He served as [[Speaker of the House of Assembly of Newfoundland and Labrador|speaker for the House of Assembly]] from 1957 until 1962, when he resigned his seat to become chairman of the Newfoundland Civil Service Commission.

